headline: 3 Things I Learned Touring the First Stargate Data Center
summary: Stargate, a partnership between OpenAI,  Oracle SoftBank  and the White House, aims to invest $500 billion over the next four years to build 10 gigawatts of capacity for AI operations in the U.S. Last week, the group announced it will construct five more data centers across the country.  There is a single portion that is currently functioning, a one-story building about the size of a library.  Seven additional buildings are being constructed.
